    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Slice the smoked sausage into rounds or half moons and add them to the slow cooker, along with the chicken thighs, oregano, thyme, paprika, cayenne, and freshly cracked pepper."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Pour the diced tomatoes and all their juices over the meat and spices in the slow cooker. Add the chicken broth and a handful of chopped fresh parsley. Stir briefly."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Place the lid on the slow cooker, turn the heat on to high, and cook for four hours."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "After four hours, the liquid in the slow cooker should be boiling. Carefully remove the chicken thighs, making sure to replace the lid quickly, shred the meat, and stir it back into the pot along with the uncooked rice. Replace the lid and let it continue to cook on high for 20-25 minutes, or until the rice has absorbed most of the liquid."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Remove the lid, test the rice to make sure it's tender, then stir to fluff the ingredients. Sprinkle the sliced green onions over top, then serve."
